-- National Australia Bank CEO Clyne quits
-- 
-- Wed Apr 02, 2014 05:47PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, April 3 (Reuters) - National Australia Bank Ltd <NAB.AX>, the country's fourth largest by market capitalisation, on Thursday announced the surprise retirement of chief executive Cameron Clyne, replacing him with the head of the group's New Zealand operations.

Andrew Thorburn, a former executive at rival Commonwealth Bank of Australia <CBA.AX> who joined NAB in 2005, will take over on Aug. 1, NAB Chairman Michael Chaney said in a statement.